            <Title>Foundation</Title>
            <Text>Thirteen years prior to the events in Genesis 17, Sarai gave Hagar as a concubine to Abram to bear children. In doing so, she displayed impatience with God’s promise and started a cycle of conflict which shook Abram’s household. Hagar ends up fleeing from Sarai but does not reach her final destination because she encounters the angel of the Lord who comforts her with God’s promise and commands her to return to Sarai. Hagar gave birth to Ishmael when Abram was 86 years old, but the child is not given to Sarai. Sarah’s ill-advised plan to build a family apart from God’s promise failed and proved true the proverb “many are the plans in the mind of a man, but it is the purpose of the Lord that will stand” (Proverbs 19:21).
