            <Title>Inscription</Title>
            <Text>The conflict between Hagar and Sarah makes it’s way into the NT as an allegory (Galatians 4:21-32). Hagar, identified with Sinai, represents the Law given to Moses. Anyone who attempts to be justified before God on the basis law-keeping or good works are offspring of the slave woman Hagar. The Law was given for a limited period in order to make us realize how much we needed a Savior. Those who accept God’s offer of salvation in Christ through faith are the children of the free woman, offspring of the promise. According to Scripture, everyone regardless of biological lineage, has the opportunity to be a spiritual child of Abraham: “for in Christ Jesus you are all sons of God, through faith. For as many of you as were baptized into Christ have put on Christ. There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free, there is no male and female, for you are all one in Christ Jesus” (Galatians 3:27-28).
