1.	Sara was childless &amp; became impatient: The causes of impatience
a.	An unfulfilled desire: Sara craved a child

Now Sarai Abram’s wife bare him no children: and she had an handmaid, an Egyptian, whose name was Hagar.

b.	A mistaken thought: That God had kept Sara barren—that God’s promise did not include her
c.	A worldly, carnal suggestion: That Abram marry Sara’s maid, Hagar, &amp; bear children

2 And Sarai said unto Abram, Behold now, the Lord hath restrained me from bearing: I pray thee, go in unto my maid; it may be that I may obtain children by her. And Abram hearkened to the voice of Sarai.

2.	Sara gave her maid to Abram: The terrible consequences of impatience
a.	A wrong plan &amp; method
b.	The collapse of faith &amp; patience

3 And Sarai Abram’s wife took Hagar her maid the Egyptian, after Abram had dwelt ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to her husband Abram to be his wife.

c.	Sinful behavior: By Abram, Sara, &amp; Hagar
1)	Immorality, adultery, &amp; polygamy

4 And he went in unto Hagar, and she conceived: and when she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her eyes.

2)	Spite, malice, insolence, reproach, scorn, a haughty spirit
3)	Jealousy &amp; blaming others

5 And Sarai said unto Abram, My wrong be upon thee: I have given my maid into thy bosom; and when she saw that she had conceived, I was despised in her eyes: the Lord judge between me and thee.

4)	Disturbed &amp; severed relationships

6 But Abram said unto Sarai, Behold, thy maid is in thy hand; do to her as it pleaseth thee. And when Sarai dealt hardly with her, she fled from her face.

3.	The Lord saved the maid, Hagar: The solution or answer to impatienceDS2

7 And the angel of the Lord found her by a fountain of water in the wilderness, by the fountain in the way to Shur.

a.	A confrontation with God

8 And he said, Hagar, Sarai’s maid, whence camest thou? and whither wilt thou go? And she said, I flee from the face of my mistress Sarai.

b.	Receiving the promises of God
1)	A special heritage: An innumerable seed

9 And the angel of the Lord said unto her, Return to thy mistress, and submit thyself under her hands.

