            <Title>Hamilton</Title>
            <Text>We take the position that circumcision is a means by which Abraham and his seed ratify God’s lordship over them. It is their identity sign as God’s covenant people. As such, circumcision is not a cognition sign, one for God’s benefit, but rather a confirmation sign, one bearing witness to Abraham’s belief that God would fulfill his promises with respect to progeny. Accordingly, Abraham’s circumcision is as much an amen to Yahweh as was his affirmation in 15:6. Hamilton, V. P. (1990). The Book of Genesis, Chapters 1–17 (pp. 471–472). Grand Rapids, MI: Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing Co.</Text>
