            <Title>Inscription</Title>
            <Text>Human sin will alway be met by either God’s mercy or judgment. Lot and his family did not merit the opportunity to escape God’s judgment, but we read that the Lord patiently endured Lot’s reluctant to let go of his life in Sodom. Like Lot we have spent many years in vanity and pride, but through God’s great patience, mercy and grace we received salvation.  Let us be mindful that choosing to live by the lusts of the flesh, eyes, and the pride of possessions rather than by faith in the promises of God will create negative consequences in our lives. Small ‘sinful’ decisions can create a slow fade that leads enormous consequences and great loss. We show also take note that the awful extent of human depravity begins will people’s failure to gratefully acknowledge God. When divine restraint is removed from the human heart the levels to which human degeneracy and depravity can descend get very low. God disciplines His children as a loving Father in order to prevent this from happening, but He will judge the impenitent like those in Sodom. </Text>
